{"type":"message","id":"b4f3f4e1","parentId":"4a34c90b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T07:04:27.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to send voice messages back and forth through Feishu, locally without calling any external APIs. They want to understand the principle and what local computer requirements are needed.\n\nLet me think about what this means:\n\n1. **Receive voice messages** - This requires Whisper (speech-to-text) running locally to transcribe voice messages sent by the user in Feishu. This is ASR (Automatic Speech Recognition).\n\n2. **Send voice messages** - This requires TTS (Text-to-Speech) running locally to generate voice responses. There's already a `sherpa-onnx-tts` skill listed in the skills config, and the user has been using TTS before.\n   \nSo the full pipeline is: receiving a voice message requires local speech-to-text (Whisper), and sending one requires local text-to-speech (like Sherpa-ONNX or Coqui TTS). For computer performance, speech-to-text is the more demanding component—real-time transcription typically needs at least 4GB of RAM and works best with a modern multi-core CPU, GPU acceleration via CUDA is optional but makes it significantly faster, and Apple Silicon with the Neural Engine handles it particularly well.\n\nText-to-speech is generally lighter, especially with simpler models like Sherpa-ONNX, which can run on CPUs with under 1GB of RAM. So the real question becomes whether the user needs GPU acceleration for Whisper or if CPU-only will suffice for their use case.\n\nI should check the docs to give a more complete picture of how OpenClaw actually handles audio messaging, but the core requirements are becoming clearer: local speech-to-text via Whisper for receiving voice messages, local text-to-speech for sending them back, and the ability to record and play audio files. The performance demands really hinge on whether they're using GPU acceleration or running everything on CPU.","thinkingSignature":"424e0cbb830f44d7b755e31ba2ee2ab9bc80c47e1c9204fea2be6136babfd461"},{"type":"text","text":"飞书语音双向本地交互的原理：\n\n## 原理\n\n```\n你发语音 → 飞书 → OpenClaw → 本地 Whisper (ASR) → 转文字 → AI处理\nAI回复 → 本地 TTS → 生成音频 → 飞书 → 你收到语音\n```\n\n两端都是本地模型，**不调用任何外部语音API**。\n\n## 性能要求\n\n**CPU 完全可以跑**，但速度有差异：\n\n| 场景 | CPU 要求 | GPU 要求 | 速度 |\n|------|---------|---------|------|\n| **ASR（听你说）** | 4核+ | 可选（大幅加速） | 实时或更快 |\n| **TTS（你说/我回复）** | 极低 | 不要 | 极快 |\n\n### ASR 方案对比\n| 模型 | 最低内存 | 推荐 | 说明 |\n|------|---------|------|------|\n| Whisper small | 2GB RAM | 4GB+ | 性价比最高 |\n| Whisper base | 1GB RAM | 2GB+ | 速度更快，准确率稍低 |\n| Whisper large | 6GB+ RAM | 8GB+ GPU | 准确率最高，CPU较慢 |\n\n### TTS 方案\n- **Sherpa-ONNX**（你已装）：CPU可用，极轻量\n- 实时合成，< 500MB 内存\n\n## 你的电脑需要什么\n\n我先看看你的环境支持情况：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_onbnhnmwzkjq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which whisper && whisper --version 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; which sherpa-onnx 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; python3 -c \"import torch; print('CUDA:', torch.cuda.is_available())\" 2>/dev/null; nproc"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":154,"output":767,"cacheRead":12896,"cacheWrite":11648,"totalTokens":25465,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777964638335,"responseId":"0648c95ff0a854f7e60e5c3f223b13c8"}}
