{"type":"message","id":"2ed0d993","parentId":"957856c2","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:05:50.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MiniMax TTS is provided by the `minimax` plugin. The config shows `minimax` in `plugins.entries` with empty config `{}`. But it doesn't have `speechProvider` configured explicitly. The models config has the minimax provider with apiKey.\n\nLet me check what the `speech-provider.js` in minimax looks like, and what the tts tool actually tries to do.\n\nActually, the error message is \"no provider registered; minimax: not configured\". This is odd because the minimax plugin has `autoEnableWhenConfiguredProviders` which includes \"minimax\". \n\nWait - maybe the issue is that the `minimax` plugin is listed in `plugins.entries` but has no config (empty `{}`), and the `speechProviders` registration needs some config to be present. Let me check the minimax speech-provider.js.\n","thinkingSignature":"71392ec914e708db2171de57d55c55ee15283b6579dc90186c0f4a682fd4eb5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g9hekx3cdr8r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -50 ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/minimax/speech-provider.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":521,"output":223,"cacheRead":31680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32424,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777968338068,"responseId":"0648d7d2adb57fe4aaf35f0bf807e708"}}
