{"type":"message","id":"1fe10996","parentId":"d1f101e8","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:06:13.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MiniMax API key is `sk-cp-...` - this is the MiniMax Chat API key, not the MiniMax TTS API key. These are different. The TTS tool error said \"minimax: not configured\" which suggests either:\n1. The TTS API key is different from the chat API key\n2. The minimax speech provider isn't enabled\n\nLet me check what the error \"no provider registered; minimax: not configured\" actually means. The TTS tool tries to use a speech provider (TTS) but the minimax speech provider isn't registered/enabled. Let me check if there's a separate config needed for minimax TTS.\n\nLet me check the minimax speech provider to understand what it needs.\n","thinkingSignature":"c9ea0cf1434c3f53868ae9fefecc2be19da07a057cb8aa6ff82346c9076e5c19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rnpxms45csc4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/minimax/ | grep speech\n# Also check if there's a separate TTS endpoint in the config\ncat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nplugins = d.get('plugins',{}).get('entries',{})\nprint('Plugin entries:', list(plugins.keys()))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":211,"output":264,"cacheRead":32192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32667,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777968361227,"responseId":"0648d7e932a52eddf9431f38f0dc40fa"}}
