{"type":"message","id":"35584e28","parentId":"c92469c0","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:06:26.103Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MiniMax plugin is listed as a plugin entry but the `config` is empty `{}`. That might mean it's not fully enabled. Let me check if there's a tts configuration needed specifically.\n\nActually, let me re-read the error: \"TTS conversion failed: : no provider registered; minimax: not configured\"\n\nThe error says \"minimax: not configured\" - this suggests the MiniMax TTS provider isn't configured properly even though the model API is configured. The TTS and the model API might have separate configurations.\n\nLet me look at what config the minimax speech-provider expects.\n","thinkingSignature":"9ee532df10c0c1470ae7614f00c07fd03a1df743077af716c9d2c4658f1d0fd1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m9zreysk3pv5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/minimax/openclaw.plugin.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(json.dumps(d.get('configSchema',{}), indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":235,"output":207,"cacheRead":32320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777968373222,"responseId":"0648d7f55026a3e19d946150f1e09b3c"}}
