{"type":"message","id":"0a9eee06","parentId":"4033c4fb","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:11:59.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files have hashed names. Let me try a different approach - let me look at the openclaw plugin config to see how to enable minimax TTS.Actually, let me just try to configure minimax TTS properly. Looking at the minimax plugin, it seems like TTS needs:\n1. The API key (we have it)\n2. The correct base URL (api.minimax.io vs api.minimaxi.com)\n\nLet me try to call the MiniMax TTS API with the current API key at the correct endpoint and see if maybe the API key works.","thinkingSignature":"d73bed282ae4470992e8dc874e857c7f96ebbe73e9993f29cf8959fd184d9f5c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43lmr0ute5qa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try MiniMax TTS API with different endpoints\nAPI_KEY=\"sk-cp-gtdRxxiZ_Qu_-9GM0xBF6UpeDvsYl8cPe4Y9mA-Xiy2GO8eBJSNPftqJdMb0Fl9OZAkY6sQR868fRUhTBV7OtwKyDfu-DzegI9-cDZERwbQGf3C5Wuvs38c\"\n\n# Try api.minimax.io (TTS endpoint)\necho \"=== Testing api.minimax.io ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/t2a_v2\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"speech-02-hd\",\"text\":\"test\",\"voice_setting\":{\"voice_id\":\"Chinese (Mandarin)_Warm_Girl\"}}' | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -10\n\necho \"=== Testing api.minimaxi.com ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://api.minimaxi.com/v1/t2a_v2\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"speech-02-hd\",\"text\":\"test\",\"voice_setting\":{\"voice_id\":\"Chinese (Mandarin)_Warm_Girl\"}}' | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23811,"output":462,"cacheRead":21559,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45832,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopRe