{"type":"message","id":"a7d3e4e5","parentId":"d9abcc89","timestamp":"2026-05-05T10:06:40.273Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HALEI just sent \"1\" as a reply to the Feishu message, confirming Feishu is working. Now let me figure out why the message tool says \"device identity required\" for wecom. This is a gateway error, not a wecom channel error. Let me check the gateway auth config.\n\nThe error says \"gateway closed (1008): device identity required\" - this means the gateway is rejecting the request because it requires device identity authentication. This is likely a security setting in the gateway config.\n\nLet me check the gateway config more carefully. The `auth.mode` is set to \"none\" but maybe we need device auth for certain operations.\n\nActually, the issue might be that the message tool via the wecom channel is being rejected at the gateway level (not the channel level). \n\nThe gateway is rejecting it with a 1008 status code, which indicates the connection itself is being closed due to the device identity requirement. I need to examine the auth configuration to understand why device identity is being enforced despite the mode being set to \"none\".\n","thinkingSignature":"3d0a40e1b7cac8f7fc35c2a2242f26447f2460aef1c05293bc6f215ceee5a7f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ytgjq9ebx4e4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1 | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54463,"output":252,"cacheRead":1344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56059,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777975582112,"responseId":"0648f41f320dac7a77104bcf5bd9cd5b"}}
