{"type":"message","id":"8e97e12f","parentId":"d82739ea","timestamp":"2026-05-05T10:08:12.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a persistent \"device identity required\" error when trying to use the wecom channel. The error happens even though the gateway is running. \n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, the \"device identity required\" error appears to be a gateway-level rejection. This might be because the wecom channel requires a specific authentication flow that needs to be completed through the UI.\n\nLooking at the error message: \"gateway closed (1008): device identity required\" - this is a WebSocket close code 1008, which means the gateway is rejecting the connection because it can't determine the device identity.\n\nThis could be because:\n1. The wecom plugin needs device authorization (pairing flow)\n2. The wecom channel requires a different auth setup than feishu\n\nLet me look at the wecom plugin configuration and see if there's something about device identity that needs to be set up. The `controlUi.dangerouslyDisableDeviceAuth` is set to true, but maybe there's another layer.\n\nActually, looking at the config - the wecom channel has `enabled: true` in the channel config section, but the plugin has `\"enabled\": true` separately. Maybe the wecom channel setup requires a pairing/authorization step.\n\nLet me check if there's a device identity file that needs to be set up, or if wecom needs a specific pairing process.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the wecom channel has its own authentication mechanism separate from the gateway auth. The wecom plugin might require device-level authorization that hasn't been completed.\n\nLet me check the openclaw docs or try to find the wecom plugin's setup requirements.\n\nBut actually - I'm overthinking this. The \"device identity required\" error from the gateway might be because the wecom channel requires the user to authorize the device through the control UI. Since we're running in a session that came from the control UI, maybe there's an issue with how that authorization transfers.\n\nLet me try something simpler - maybe restarting the gateway fresh will clear the stale state.\n\n\nI could try toggling the wecom channel off and back on in the config, but that might cause issues. The real problem seems to be that the wecom plugin has a device authorization requirement that hasn't been satisfied. The control UI should have completed this pairing process, but there's likely a stale state preventing a clean connection.\n\nLet me check if the wecom plugin has a device ID or pairing file that needs to be reset. I should also look at what the wecom-openclaw-plugin actually requires in terms of configuration. The \"device identity required\" error appearing specifically when the wecom message tool is used suggests the wecom channel has its own authentication layer that's interfering with the gateway connection.\n\nI need to check if there's a device identity setup required for wecom that differs from the gateway's auth settings, or if the control UI needs to complete a device pairing step for wecom specifically.\n","thinkingSignature":"bc785516593a130bfdc1b0d1f636c198a5f37c47ae8279c0d5c66153fa6599bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1gj8q2ov66ho_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -newer /tmp -exec ls -l {} \\; 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"device|identity|pair|auth\" | head -10\nls /home/halei/.openclaw/ | grep -iE \"device|identity|pair|auth\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":179,"output":684,"cacheRead":62848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63711,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777975666032,"responseId":"0648f472ee7fbaf035ad83b3e1bc07d4"}}
