{"type":"message","id":"81e75166","parentId":"4f3d79e2","timestamp":"2026-05-05T10:08:47.756Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `device identity required` error is happening when sending to wecom but not feishu. Looking at the logs more carefully:\n\n1. The gateway restarts and has `auth.mode = \"none\"` (no auth)\n2. But the error says `device identity required`\n\nLooking at the log entry:\n```\n\"Gateway auth mode=none explicitly configured; all gateway connections are unauthenticated.\"\n```\n\nSo after restart, auth mode is none. But before that, there were earlier errors.\n\nThe key thing is - why does feishu work but wecom doesn't?\n\nLooking at the error context more carefully - the `gateway closed (1008): device identity required` happens when I try to send a message tool call to wecom. \n\nI'm wondering if the wecom channel requires device identity to be established first, while feishu doesn't. The logs mention something about the channel plugin needing to declare channelConfigs metadata. This might be a configuration issue where wecom expects certain setup that isn't being met. Let me check the gateway config to see if there's something specific about how these channels are initialized differently.\n\nLooking at the error timestamp and the gateway restart, it seems like the gateway was still initializing when the request came in. The device identity might have been needed during that startup window. But the fact that feishu works fine suggests the real problem is with how wecom is configured - maybe the plugin isn't properly registered or there's a mismatch in the channelConfigs that prevents it from loading correctly.\n\nThe device identity error appearing specifically for wecom is telling. Even though auth is set to none in the config, the wecom plugin might be enforcing its own device identity check separately. The error occurs during message tool calls to wecom, which suggests the plugin is trying to validate something that isn't there. I should check whether the wecom plugin configuration has changed recently or if there's a stale plugin entry causing conflicts - I see there was a restart at 17:22 after removing the weixin plugin, so there might be a mismatch between what the config expects and what the plugin actually provides. The warning suggests the wecom plugin is missing the channelConfigs metadata, which might be why it's not loading properly. But this shouldn't affect outgoing messages—only incoming events. Looking at the error context, when I try to send a message to wecom, it's requesting device identity before the gateway accepts the connection. The feishu sends work fine though, which suggests the gateway might be restarting when this error occurs. Let me check if there are any running gateway processes and whether the config changes are taking effect.\n\nActually, I think the real issue is that I removed the weixin plugin from the config earlier, and that change might have triggered a config reload that's causing problems with the gateway's initialization.\n\nLet me just restart the gateway cleanly to see if that resolves it.\n","thinkingSignature":"af852aedc99a181232c38e415a55a12a04da410f85e61b4729faeb8808324679"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jwjp6z4z00cs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway stop 2>&1; sleep 3; openclaw gateway start 2>&1 &\nsleep 8 && openclaw gateway status 2>&1 | grep -E \"Runtime|state|Listening|Connectivity\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":663,"output":655,"cacheRead":63232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64550,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777975701278,"responseId":"0648f495430956793466be3f99cec624"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f984bb2d","parentId":"81e75166","timestamp":"2026-05-05T10:08:55.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jwjp6z4z00cs_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"│\n◇  Config warnings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.wecom-openclaw-plugin: plugin wecom-openclaw-plugin:      │\n│    channel plugin manifest declares wecom without channelConfigs             │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin: plugin openclaw-weixin: channel          │\n│    plugin manifest declares openclaw-weixin without channelConfigs           │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: channel plugin manifest            │\n│    declares feishu without channelConfigs metadata; add                      │\n│    openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema and setup            │\n│    surfaces work before runtime loads                                        │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: duplicate plugin id detected;      │\n│    global plugin will be overridden by global plugin                         │\n│    (/home/halei/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_mo  │\n│  dules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/index.js)                             │\n│  - plugins.entries.wecom-openclaw-plugin: plugin wecom-openclaw-plugin:      │\n│    channel plugin manifest declares wecom without channelConfigs             │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin: plugin openclaw-weixin: channel          │\n│    plugin manifest declares openclaw-weixin without channelConfigs           │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: channel plugin manifest            │\n│    declares feishu without channelConfigs metadata; add                      │\n│    openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema and setup            │\n│    surfaces work before runtime loads                                        │\n│  - plugins.allow: plugin not found: wecom (stale config entry ignored;       │\n│    remove it from plugins config)                                            │\n│                                                                              │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\n\nCommand aborted by signal SIGTERM"}],"details":{"status":"failed","exitCode":null,"durationMs":7687,"aggregated":"│\n◇  Config warnings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.wecom-openclaw-plugin: plugin wecom-openclaw-plugin:      │\n│    channel plugin manifest declares wecom without channelConfigs             │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin: plugin openclaw-weixin: channel          │\n│    plugin manifest declares openclaw-weixin without channelConfigs           │\n│    metadata; add openclaw.plugin.json#channelConfigs so config schema        │\n│    and setup surfaces work before runtime loads                              │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: chan