{"type":"message","id":"9cd1de8b","parentId":"9a44bee7","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:13:33.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still getting device identity required. But I notice the config warnings mentioned:\n\n```\n- plugins.allow: plugin not found: wecom (stale config entry ignored; remove it from plugins config)\n```\n\nThe wecom plugin is referenced in `plugins.allow` but the actual plugin entry is `wecom-openclaw-plugin`. Let me check the config.\n\nActually the issue might be something different. The `device identity required` error happens when the Gateway is running but the agent can't authenticate. The fact that feishu works but wecom doesn't is interesting.\n\nWait - actually looking at the logs more carefully, the issue is that my current agent session is getting \"device identity required\" when trying to call the message tool for wecom. \n\nSo feishu succeeds with the same connection. The error is specifically about device identity. Looking at the Gateway config warnings about `plugins.allow: plugin not found: wecom`, I think the wecom plugin configuration might be stale or pointing to the wrong plugin ID. The Gateway is binding to loopback and reports running, but something in the wecom setup isn't matching what's actually available.","thinkingSignature":"b54731d7b9bea5c0937953ee43f8b2d799a771a97573414f80c182818f78a301"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6nixr00nwfxx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('plugins.allow:', json.dumps(d.get('plugins',{}).get('allow',[]), indent=2))\nprint('wecom channel:', json.dumps(d.get('channels',{}).get('wecom',{}), indent=2))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48402,"output":331,"cacheRead":21192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69925,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777983204224,"responseId":"064911e4ef651bee0001775a3b46ad05"}}
