{"type":"message","id":"468b6971","parentId":"16df896a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:13:45.546Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem! The `plugins.allow` has `\"wecom\"` but the actual plugin id is `\"wecom-openclaw-plugin\"`. However, the `channels.wecom` config also has `secret` field but the wecom plugin in `plugins.entries` uses `wecom-openclaw-plugin` as the key. And there's also a separate `openclaw-weixin` in plugins.entries.\n\nThe config is a mess:\n- `channels.wecom` - has botId and secret (correct channel config)\n- `plugins.entries.wecom-openclaw-plugin` - the actual plugin\n- `plugins.allow` has both `\"wecom-openclaw-plugin\"` and `\"wecom\"`\n\n\n- `channels.openclaw-weixin` - was removed but the plugin is still there\n- `plugins.allow` includes both `wecom` and `wecom-openclaw-plugin`\n\nThe real issue is that the `message` tool is failing with \"gateway closed (1008): device identity required\" which seems to be a websocket authentication problem rather than a plugin configuration issue. This error occurs when the Gateway rejects the connection attempt, and it's happening consistently across both wecom and feishu channels despite the Gateway reporting as running.\n\nThe websocket connection is failing at the Gateway level before it can even process the message, and it's isolated to this agent session—the user can still access the Control UI and send messages through other channels. This suggests the problem is specific to how this session is attempting to reconnect after the restart, rather than a general Gateway availability issue.","thinkingSignature":"4fb721be987c531cab48b50ce3e97ffc48952b078b16973dd599515cd2d49d43"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aunnokpnc77e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-05.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line:\n        continue\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        msg = d.get('message','')\n        t = d.get('time','')[-8:]\n        if any(x in msg.lower() for x in ['device','identity','wecom','connect','error']):\n            print(f'{t} {msg[:120]}')\n    except:\n        pass\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48857,"output":470,"cacheRead":21192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70519,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777983213990,"responseId":"064911ee8da6ba015e78c9ec6271bd48"}}
