{"type":"message","id":"7cd4c135","parentId":"eb750908","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:13:53.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key error is: \"feishu[kiit]: failed to dispatch message: TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'registry')\"\n\nAnd also \"gateway connect failed: GatewayClientRequestError: device identity required\" - this is when THIS agent session tries to connect to the gateway via the message tool.\n\nThe \"device identity required\" seems to be a session-specific issue. The gateway itself is running but there's something about how this agent session authenticates.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the Gateway restart happened, and after restart the agent reconnected. But when the agent tries to call the message tool (to send to wecom), it gets \"device identity required\". \n\nSo feishu messages work fine through the message tool, but wecom fails with that same error. The difference is that wecom might not have a valid route or session binding set up in the config, whereas feishu does. Let me check the current gateway status to see what's actually happening with the connections.","thinkingSignature":"6b79d967748f996217954aa1c3bd792b06c0c28a3a4e5ca2bebc018782ccb864"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hdfrx7y8xero_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway status 2>&1 | grep -E \"Runtime|state|Listening|Connectivity\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49768,"output":250,"cacheRead":21192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777983226215,"responseId":"064911faa2714f20e7ad294c5e2644be"}}
