{"type":"message","id":"8f45e7d9","parentId":"dbc52289","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:14:24.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Feishu works. The problem is specifically with the wecom channel. Let me check the wecom channel configuration more carefully. The error \"gateway closed (1008): device identity required\" is being returned by the message tool. Let me look at what the wecom channel config actually requires.Looking at the openclaw.json earlier:- `channels.wecom` has `botId` and `secret` but no `accountId` or `account`\n- There's no binding for wecom channel to any agent\n\nThe feishu channel has a binding in the `bindings` array and the wecom doesn't. Maybe that's part of the issue, but the error is \"device identity required\" not \"no route\".\n\n\nI'm wondering if the wecom plugin itself might not be fully loaded. Looking at the gateway config warnings, I see the wecom plugin is registered but missing some metadata configuration that other plugins have. The error about the gateway being closed seems to be happening at the websocket level before the message tool even tries to process the wecom request.\n\nSo if feishu works fine with the same gateway setup, the difference must be in how each channel handles the connection. Maybe the wecom channel is trying to establish its own websocket connection to the WeCom server and that's failing in a way that causes the gateway to reject it with that 1008 error.\n\nThe real issue might be that I'm sending to the wecom plugin, but that plugin isn't properly configured or is failing to initialize. I should verify the wecom plugin is actually enabled and loaded, or consider just removing the wecom channel entirely since the user said they're not using it anyway. But they specifically asked why wechat isn't sending, so I need to figure out what's actually broken with the wecom integration. I'm noticing the wecom plugin is listed in the allowlist but the actual plugin ID doesn't match what's registered, so maybe the message tool is validating the channel name against the plugin name and failing because of that mismatch. I should check if the wecom plugin has the right permissions and capabilities to handle outgoing messages, and whether it requires additional authentication like WeCom's corp ID and agent ID that might be missing from the config.\n\nLet me restart the gateway cleanly to clear out any stale state, and also verify whether the wecom channel was actually removed earlier or if it's still lingering in the channels config.","thinkingSignature":"924762911ef9c822429b60c3795329791e15269dbc4ee13daf5182d7b55fbd3c"},{"type":"text","text":"飞书正常，企业微信报错。让我查一下日志看看 wecom 那边具体报什么错。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxpyok9ugi2m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -100 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-05.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line: continue\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[11:19]\n        msg = d.get('message','')\n        if any(x in msg.lower() for x in ['wecom','wechat','sender','dispatch','channel']):\n            print(f'{t} {msg[:200]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50438,"output":659,"cacheRead":21192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72289,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777983245498,"responseId":"0649120ddfeae436a62c36ba43573620"}}
