{"type":"message","id":"89c976ff","parentId":"c427f809","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:51:35.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The wecom channel is still in the config. The issue is that when I tried to remove the openclaw-weixin channel earlier, I removed it successfully, but wecom channel seems to still be there. But the logs said \"channels.wecom: unknown channel id: wecom\" which means the wecom plugin isn't loaded to register that channel ID.\n\nLet me check if wecom plugin is actually installed/enabled:\n- plugins.entries has no wecom entry (only memory-core, minimax, feishu, openclaw-weixin)\n- but wecom is in plugins.allow\n\nSo the wecom plugin is in the allow list but not actually enabled. And there's no wecom plugin installed at all - there's just the openclaw-weixin (微信) plugin, not the wecom (企业微信) plugin.\n\n\nI need to clarify whether the user actually has the 企业微信 plugin installed or if they're trying to use 微信. The \"unknown channel id: wecom\" error suggests the wecom plugin isn't loaded, so let me try sending a test message to WeChat to see if it's actually functional.","thinkingSignature":"da72a008c79ae97915f2f0d62c6e9af381419d44365f9f0626e0cbaea928c4f8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9cwjed3n0019_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/halei/.openclaw -maxdepth 4 -name \"openclaw.plugin.json\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"wechat\\|wecom\\|weixin\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51378,"output":302,"cacheRead":21934,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73614,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777985485725,"responseId":"06491acea7c0bdbac21aea85a04de221"}}
