{"type":"message","id":"378b4bf0","parentId":"26e95700","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:51:48.459Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's no wecom plugin installed. The channel \"wecom\" is in the config but no plugin is loaded that registers it. The only plugin related to this is \"openclaw-weixin\" which is the personal WeChat plugin, not 企业微信 (WeCom).\n\nLet me try to send via the channel with the correct name. Since wecom isn't registered by any loaded plugin, trying to send via \"wecom\" channel won't work. But let me try \"openclaw-weixin\" to see if that works.\n\nActually, the current issue is that the wecom channel is in the config but no plugin registers it. This was probably a stale config from a previous setup. The `channels.wecom` entry references a plugin that isn't installed/enabled.\n \nLet me verify whether the wecom plugin is actually available to be enabled, since the channel config points to something that doesn't seem to exist in the system.","thinkingSignature":"e0d549589ed84c45a3294612237761ca2295facd7144f6939ca146f200b9941f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4vdjx6m2j55c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/ 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"wecom|wechat|weixin\"\nls ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/ 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"wecom|wechat|weixin\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51718,"output":271,"cacheRead":21934,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73923,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777985495857,"responseId":"06491adbf5e46b5ecd7ea7f943b9dbe6"}}
