{"type":"message","id":"87e86e85","parentId":"dc31245e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:52:10.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the @wecom directory is empty. And @tencent-weixin has openclaw-weixin. So the 企业微信 (WeCom) plugin is NOT installed - only the 微信 (WeChat) plugin is there.\n\nSo the wecom channel config is pointing to a plugin that doesn't exist (empty directory). That's why it says \"unknown channel id: wecom\".\n\nThe current situation:\n- wecom channel is configured with botId and secret\n- But the wecom plugin (@wecom/wecom-openclaw-plugin) is not actually installed (empty directory)\n- Only the personal WeChat plugin (@tencent-weixin/openclaw-weixin) is installed\n\n\n- The wecom channel config needs to be removed since the plugin isn't there, and we should clarify whether the user wants to set up 企业微信 or just use 飞书 for now. Let me check if wecom was previously working before the restart by looking at the logs.","thinkingSignature":"adf52f5374e7e0ba49ca9ade71e85c8884e00f5c0d2cc5911833c87c6a58728b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dlqlrqnkknk0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"wecom.*login\\|wecom.*二维码\\|二维码.*wecom\\|Channel.*wecom\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-*.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        print(d.get('time','')[:19], d.get('message','')[:150])\n    except:\n        print(line[:150])\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52494,"output":325,"cacheRead":21934,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74753,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777985520741,"responseId":"06491af1231a5f2774af58558355194c"}}
