{"type":"message","id":"65eed698","parentId":"24c72327","timestamp":"2026-05-05T13:50:23.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The critical error is:\n```\nfeishu[kiit]: failed to dispatch message: TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'registry')\n```\n\nThis means the feishu channel is trying to dispatch a message but something is undefined. Also, the liveness warning shows event loop delays and the phase is stuck at `channels.feis` (feishu).\n\nAlso there's:\n```\nChannel login failed: Error: Failed to start login: TypeError: fetch failed\n```\n\nThis suggests the feishu channel can't even log in - network issue fetching from feishu servers.\n\nBut wait - the user says messages aren't getting replies. The feishu plugin seems to be partially loaded (it's at `phase=channels.feis`) but there's an error with `registry` being undefined. \n\n\nThe core issue appears to be that the feishu channel's login process is failing due to network connectivity problems reaching Feishu's servers, which then cascades into the dispatch failure when messages try to go through. The event loop is also backing up with significant delays, making it harder for the system to recover. The issue might be a version mismatch between the two Feishu plugin installations—the global installation and the staged one could be conflicting. I should try reinstalling the feishu plugin or at least verify that a restart with the cleaned config actually loads the feishu channel properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"9aaaaa688fb5eadb478f93649d66be21b1112d47b6c2b5e5f19de669eedf0f86"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fk47317wwjls_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check feishu plugin state\nls /home/halei/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/ 2>/dev/null | head -10\nls /home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/dist/ 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\n# Check what feis