{"type":"message","id":"beef807e","parentId":"818cfdca","timestamp":"2026-05-05T13:54:48.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu plugin has a very detailed schema. I can see it has `blockStreaming` and `blockStreamingCoalesce` options. The `streaming: true` at the top level is for the channel-level streaming, but there's also account-level streaming options.\n\nLooking at the configSchema properties, I see `blockStreaming` is a boolean and also has `blockStreamingCoalesce` object. The `blockStreaming` is likely what controls whether streaming responses are sent as partial message updates or as complete blocks.\n\nThe current config has `streaming: true` at the channel level but doesn't mention `blockStreaming`. The issue might be that the streaming is configured but the `blockStreaming` is not, which means the streaming is working but without block-level control.\n \nI should check if the kiit account has its own streaming configuration that might be overriding the channel-level setting, or if `blockStreaming` needs to be explicitly enabled to make the partial updates work properly.","thinkingSignature":"57f6a7580a0be9ef90289a4746e3d83c0d18424b839cf6d0e775b9d33dae3293"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n飞书配置里 streaming 是开的，但没设置 `blockStreaming`——这可能是问题所在。让我看看 account 级别有没有覆盖：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5gbv2pif4s1m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nkiit = d.get('channels',{}).get('feishu',{}).get('accounts',{}).get('kiit',{})\nprint('kiit account config:', json.dumps(kiit, indent=2))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9274,"output":328,"cacheRead":88640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777989274161,"responseId":"0649299ab9bfc3ef2037350f8cd4