{"type":"message","id":"a7a63bfa","parentId":"28def82d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T14:16:22.725Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The document has only 2 blocks total - this is unusual. It seems like the document might be using some kind of dynamic content that requires the full client-side rendering of the docx. The API only sees the structural blocks but not the actual content.\n\nLet me try to get the actual content through another approach. Let me try using the document content version history or another endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"5fd84a677b08263a65a1417f05bbfeb6f80347228f3b33dae1269b0e2f322944"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_73vjcy4g0xbj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"DOC_TOKEN=\"JQXqd7vIIoTe3jxPAZ0cBViYnNi\"\nTOKEN=\"t-g10455laLNCINI3M754RGERNY62VIV5LJLLRSJFJ\"\n\n# Try with user access token approach - get meta first\ncurl -s -X GET \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/docx/v1/documents/${DOC_TOKEN}\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('code:', d.get('code'))\nprint('title:', d.get('data',{}).get('document',{}).get('title'))\n\" 2>&1\n\n# Try a different approach - using the document read content API\ncurl -s \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/docx/v1/documents/${DOC_TOKEN}\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":313,"output":317,"cacheRead":115232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115862,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777990573802,"responseId":"06492eae012381537d089e26ba5e3c4a"}}
